{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"89f8af44-47a2-42e0-9c94-9dd593922620","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped the VSTest compatibility layer by default.**\n\nStarting with MSTest.Sdk 4.0.0, the SDK uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform exclusively and no longer ships the VSTest adapter/runner bridge. This means `vstest.console` (and `dotnet test` in legacy VSTest mode) cannot discover or run tests from these projects.\n\n**Your options:**\n\n1. **Re-enable VSTest support** — add this to your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>\n   ```\n   or explicitly opt back in:\n   ```xml\n   <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   ```\n\n2. **Switch your CI to use `dotnet test` with the new platform** — modern `dotnet test` (SDK 8.0.400+) supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively. Replace `vstest.console` invocations with:\n   ```\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n\n3. **Pin to MSTest.Sdk/3.x** if you aren't ready to migrate your pipeline.\n\nThe recommended path forward is option 2 — retire `vstest.console` and use `dotnet test`, which now delegates to Microsoft.Testing.Platform directly.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bfc7b125-ddba-4bfa-9c9e-1a555ab6a113","outputTokens":330,"requestId":"BD05:1A8D4E:1FC148F:240A718:6A07D67A"},"id":"4ed0839f-d4e0-48a2-bf58-6685fa245e82","timestamp":"2026-05-16T02:29:22.278Z","parentId":"bcd22872-17c5-45de-af86-85d028bdc60d"}
